1
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:31,880
[The Dark Romance]

2
00:01:32,120 --> 00:01:34,910
[Episode 17]

3
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:26,640
Why are you sitting here?

4
00:02:27,560 --> 00:02:28,360
What's wrong?

5
00:02:30,079 --> 00:02:31,410
Are you feeling unwell?

6
00:02:35,870 --> 00:02:37,470
I thought about it all night.

7
00:02:37,870 --> 00:02:38,840
You are right.

8
00:02:40,030 --> 00:02:41,280
We are the same.

9
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:44,480
I had actually thought about...

10
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:47,630
completely forgetting Ding Zhibo
for the rest of my life,

11
00:02:47,630 --> 00:02:49,290
not telling anyone about him,

12
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:50,680
not even you.

13
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:54,030
Both of us

14
00:02:55,870 --> 00:02:56,630
carry lifelong wounds and shame

15
00:02:56,630 --> 00:02:58,910
that we don't want others to know about.

16
00:03:00,030 --> 00:03:00,710
So...

17
00:03:01,470 --> 00:03:02,240
I'm sorry.

18
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:07,160
I have no right to criticize you.

19
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:22,000
You don't have to force yourself

20
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,260
to accept me like this.

21
00:03:24,030 --> 00:03:24,520
Really.

22
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:26,600
You don't have to.

23
00:03:26,760 --> 00:03:27,820
But I'm willing to.

24
00:03:27,870 --> 00:03:29,079
I'm willing to accept you.

25
00:03:29,079 --> 00:03:30,120
I am.

26
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:32,650
Just like you accepted me completely.

27
00:03:38,280 --> 00:03:39,750
We both have wounds.

28
00:03:41,870 --> 00:03:43,240
Healing together

29
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:46,460
is always faster than doing it alone.

30
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:49,430
I love you.

31
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:54,680
Your protection and support
are very important to me.

32
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:03,540
You said before

33
00:04:04,080 --> 00:04:05,150
that no matter how many hardships

34
00:04:05,150 --> 00:04:06,840
you went through
or how misunderstood you were,

35
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:08,150
you never wanted to give up.

36
00:04:08,150 --> 00:04:10,870
Me too. I don't want to give up either.

37
00:04:11,240 --> 00:04:12,750
I've been struggling to move forward,

38
00:04:12,750 --> 00:04:14,120
and that's how I met you.

39
00:04:17,870 --> 00:04:19,200
There's one more thing.

40
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:21,160
I lied to you.

41
00:04:26,680 --> 00:04:28,940
When I gave you the marriage certificate

42
00:04:29,350 --> 00:04:31,690
and said I could accept you leaving me,

43
00:04:33,960 --> 00:04:35,050
I was lying.

44
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:39,100
I was really afraid you would say yes.

45
00:04:40,420 --> 00:04:41,560
I was really afraid

46
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:42,480
you would actually leave me.

47
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:43,750
No, I wouldn't.

48
00:04:44,510 --> 00:04:45,240
I wouldn't.

49
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:47,500
I really can't imagine life without you.

50
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:49,890
You said

51
00:04:51,270 --> 00:04:52,190
we are

52
00:04:53,630 --> 00:04:55,960
the best gifts
heaven has given each of us.

53
00:04:56,360 --> 00:04:57,750
I won't leave you.

54
00:04:58,720 --> 00:04:59,540
Thank you.

55
00:05:00,890 --> 00:05:02,690
Thank you for not giving up on me.

56
00:05:03,480 --> 00:05:06,080
Thank you for still being willing
to be my wife.

57
00:05:06,510 --> 00:05:07,470
I am willing.

58
00:05:07,630 --> 00:05:08,630
Of course I am.

59
00:05:11,560 --> 00:05:12,960
I can't live without you.

60
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:13,720
Thank you.

61
00:05:14,190 --> 00:05:15,820
I can't live without you.

62
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:18,120
I love you.

63
00:05:19,190 --> 00:05:20,840
We must be together forever.

64
00:05:20,980 --> 00:05:22,600
-We can't be apart.
-We will.

65
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,930
I won't let you leave me.

66
00:05:26,260 --> 00:05:26,990
I love you.

67
00:05:27,190 --> 00:05:28,690
I won't leave you.

68
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:29,960
I love you.

69
00:05:30,190 --> 00:05:31,090
I love you too.

70
00:05:36,460 --> 00:05:37,100
Yuan!

71
00:05:37,640 --> 00:05:38,520
Yuan!

72
00:05:39,070 --> 00:05:39,870
Yuan!

73
00:05:40,390 --> 00:05:41,240
What's wrong?

74
00:05:41,680 --> 00:05:42,480
What's wrong?

75
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:49,150
Yuan!

76
00:05:49,540 --> 00:05:50,060
Yuan!

77
00:05:50,330 --> 00:05:50,890
Yuan!

78
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:54,800
Yuan!

79
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:55,830
Yuan!

80
00:05:56,870 --> 00:05:57,770
Yuan!

81
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:58,670
Yuan!

82
00:06:10,040 --> 00:06:10,920
You're awake?

83
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:13,500
Does the wound still hurt?

84
00:06:16,230 --> 00:06:17,370
Do you need my help?

85
00:06:17,750 --> 00:06:19,270
No, I can handle it.

86
00:06:20,750 --> 00:06:22,550
The doctor said you need to rest.

87
00:06:24,630 --> 00:06:26,090
If I let you do everything,

88
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:27,870
won't my recovery

89
00:06:27,870 --> 00:06:29,160
take longer?

90
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,800
My cooking isn't that bad, is it?

91
00:06:32,870 --> 00:06:34,270
I kind of hope it is.

92
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:36,750
That way,
I can keep getting an upset stomach

93
00:06:36,750 --> 00:06:38,280
and won't have to go to work.

94
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:42,430
Let me see.

95
00:06:44,270 --> 00:06:46,530
You look like you've been knocked silly.

96
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:55,340
I want to go back and visit Mom.

97
00:06:57,830 --> 00:06:58,890
You miss her again?

98
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:00,120
No.

99
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:03,330
I'm talking about your mom.

100
00:07:04,040 --> 00:07:05,070
Your real mom.

101
00:07:06,480 --> 00:07:08,680
I want to take Jiale to see her.

102
00:07:15,190 --> 00:07:17,920
Your mom must be very lonely
back home by herself.

103
00:07:18,270 --> 00:07:19,540
If she is willing,

104
00:07:19,630 --> 00:07:20,920
she can move in with us.

105
00:07:21,920 --> 00:07:23,180
Do you really think so?

106
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:28,360
My mom is gone.

107
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:31,030
I really regret it.

108
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:34,800
I missed out on a lot of time with her.

109
00:07:36,190 --> 00:07:38,390
I don't want you to have the same regret.

110
00:07:38,750 --> 00:07:41,040
Don't worry, I will treat your mom

111
00:07:41,480 --> 00:07:43,640
just like my own.

112
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:46,270
Thank you.

113
00:07:47,390 --> 00:07:50,250
If my mom heard what you just said,

114
00:07:51,070 --> 00:07:52,530
she would be very touched.

115
00:07:53,310 --> 00:07:54,720
If she sees Jiale,

116
00:07:55,270 --> 00:07:57,130
she'll probably be even happier.

117
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:06,540
It's the hospital.

118
00:08:09,070 --> 00:08:11,530
I still have a bunch of things
waiting for me.

119
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:15,800
Honey.

120
00:08:16,390 --> 00:08:18,050
When this busy period is over,

121
00:08:18,270 --> 00:08:19,680
you, me, and Jiale—

122
00:08:20,830 --> 00:08:23,630
let's go back to my hometown together
to see my mom.

123
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:24,720
Okay.

124
00:08:39,669 --> 00:08:40,240
Hello?

125
00:08:41,669 --> 00:08:42,470
What's wrong?

126
00:08:42,659 --> 00:08:43,980
Well... Yuan...

127
00:08:44,150 --> 00:08:47,200
seems to be getting sicker these days.

128
00:08:47,480 --> 00:08:49,610
Sometimes she has epileptic seizures

129
00:08:49,720 --> 00:08:51,480
that won't stop for a long time.

130
00:08:51,910 --> 00:08:54,820
Those medicines don't seem to work either.

131
00:08:56,390 --> 00:09:00,450
Every time she takes them, she complains
of a headache and wants to vomit.

132
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:03,610
Should we send her to the hospital again?

133
00:09:03,720 --> 00:09:05,440
Are you the doctor, or am I?

134
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:08,110
It takes time for the medicine to work.

135
00:09:08,110 --> 00:09:09,640
Just feed her as I said.

136
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:10,790
Don't miss a single day,

137
00:09:10,790 --> 00:09:13,120
and don't miss a single pill, understand?

138
00:09:13,870 --> 00:09:14,510
Got it.

139
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:23,180
I didn't have time to tell you before.

140
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:25,280
I got married.

141
00:09:27,390 --> 00:09:28,120
Married?

142
00:09:30,030 --> 00:09:31,000
Who is your wife?

143
00:09:31,910 --> 00:09:33,310
She is a college teacher.

144
00:09:34,390 --> 00:09:35,390
She's a good girl.

145
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:37,390
I'll find some time later

146
00:09:37,390 --> 00:09:38,650
to bring her to see you.

147
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:42,720
Okay, sounds good.

148
00:09:43,910 --> 00:09:45,170
Take care of my sister.

149
00:09:46,380 --> 00:09:47,510
Don't make me worry.

150
00:10:09,290 --> 00:10:11,550
[Li Changning]

151
00:10:13,870 --> 00:10:15,050
[Bachelor's Degree Certificate,
Lihai University of Science & Technology]

152
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:19,630
Ms. Yan, I graduated.

153
00:10:19,630 --> 00:10:20,480
If it weren't for you,

154
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:21,960
I definitely couldn't have done it.

155
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:23,150
Thank you so much.

156
00:10:23,270 --> 00:10:25,840
It's a pity you didn't come
to the graduation ceremony.

157
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:26,870
I miss you so much.

158
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:30,520
Li Changning graduated?

159
00:10:31,670 --> 00:10:32,530
She's amazing.

160
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:34,520
Why didn't you go see her?

161
00:10:37,270 --> 00:10:39,130
The school didn't ask me to attend

162
00:10:39,750 --> 00:10:41,550
the graduation ceremony at all.

163
00:10:45,870 --> 00:10:46,600
Makes sense.

164
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:50,000
From the school's perspective,

165
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:51,450
I can understand it.

166
00:10:54,910 --> 00:10:56,970
You also think I shouldn't have gone.

167
00:10:58,960 --> 00:11:00,200
You can't expect everyone

168
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:01,510
to know you like I do.

169
00:11:02,390 --> 00:11:03,790
Right now, to the school,

170
00:11:04,670 --> 00:11:07,440
you're indeed like a hot potato.

171
00:11:11,480 --> 00:11:12,790
Maybe it

172
00:11:12,790 --> 00:11:13,920
sounds harsh to you,

173
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:17,240
but if it were you,

174
00:11:18,510 --> 00:11:19,510
what would you do?

175
00:11:20,910 --> 00:11:21,510
After all,

176
00:11:24,550 --> 00:11:25,320
that person

177
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:27,960
made all the letters public.

178
00:11:29,510 --> 00:11:31,840
I know what you went through emotionally.

179
00:11:31,870 --> 00:11:32,670
I also know

180
00:11:32,670 --> 00:11:34,200
how you gradually

181
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:35,440
fell into his trap.

182
00:11:36,390 --> 00:11:37,990
But the school doesn't know.

183
00:11:38,050 --> 00:11:39,330
Others don't know.

184
00:11:39,870 --> 00:11:41,270
In the eyes of outsiders,

185
00:11:41,320 --> 00:11:44,390
you're just a homewrecker who pursued
someone else's husband

186
00:11:44,390 --> 00:11:45,200
and a liar.

187
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:54,280
With your abilities,

188
00:11:55,080 --> 00:11:57,280
you can totally take a break for a while.

189
00:11:59,270 --> 00:12:01,670
It will also let
the public outcry die down.

190
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:04,870
Change your environment and start afresh.

191
00:12:08,550 --> 00:12:09,670
Are you saying

192
00:12:10,670 --> 00:12:11,790
I should resign?

193
00:12:18,720 --> 00:12:19,450
Why should I?

194
00:12:20,390 --> 00:12:22,590
I'm not the one who committed the crime.

195
00:12:25,790 --> 00:12:27,200
Throwing a childish temper tantrum at me

196
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:28,400
won't do you any good.

197
00:12:29,750 --> 00:12:31,080
Objectively speaking,

198
00:12:31,390 --> 00:12:33,380
you didn't get your professional title,

199
00:12:33,380 --> 00:12:35,720
so even without all this mess,

200
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:37,870
you might not have been able to stay.

201
00:12:37,870 --> 00:12:39,150
Whether you leave now or not is simply

202
00:12:39,150 --> 00:12:42,210
a matter of who takes the initiative
—the school or you.

203
00:12:43,150 --> 00:12:44,810
Should I just surrender then?

204
00:12:47,550 --> 00:12:49,000
Alright, alright.

205
00:12:49,720 --> 00:12:51,720
After all, it's your own career.

206
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:54,660
I'm just helping you
weigh the pros and cons.

207
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:56,840
The final decision is yours.

208
00:12:58,720 --> 00:13:01,510
I don't want to see my wife wronged,

209
00:13:02,360 --> 00:13:04,720
returning to school full of enthusiasm

210
00:13:05,150 --> 00:13:06,670
only to be shut out by them.

211
00:13:16,960 --> 00:13:18,760
Forget it. I won't say anything.

212
00:13:40,520 --> 00:13:49,650
[July 11, 2019, Thursday]

213
00:14:10,280 --> 00:14:14,990
[July 11, 2019, Thursday]

214
00:14:21,330 --> 00:14:24,730
[July 11, 2019, Thursday]

215
00:14:56,390 --> 00:14:56,960
You're right,

216
00:14:56,960 --> 00:14:57,440
Honey.

217
00:14:58,790 --> 00:14:59,550
If I go back,

218
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:03,000
I might just be humiliating myself.

219
00:15:03,610 --> 00:15:05,810
You might not like what I'm about to say,

220
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:07,540
but I have to say it.

221
00:15:09,010 --> 00:15:10,550
I can support you and Jiale.

222
00:15:12,060 --> 00:15:15,060
I don't want my wife
to suffer any injustice out there.

223
00:15:16,870 --> 00:15:17,440
Honey.

224
00:15:18,750 --> 00:15:21,720
I shouldn't have lost my temper with you.
I'm sorry.

225
00:15:26,910 --> 00:15:27,510
It's okay.

226
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:30,390
I'm not mad at you.

227
00:15:32,550 --> 00:15:33,350
It's my fault.

228
00:15:34,270 --> 00:15:35,530
Please don't blame me.

229
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:38,330
I'm not blaming you.

230
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:41,130
Think about it.

231
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:43,200
Think carefully.

232
00:15:45,090 --> 00:15:49,730
[International Medical Center]

233
00:15:50,360 --> 00:15:54,150
Patient No. 21, please go to Room 1.

234
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:55,720
Hello.

235
00:15:56,910 --> 00:15:57,400
Hello.

236
00:15:58,080 --> 00:15:59,140
Please take a seat.

237
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:00,910
Put it here.

238
00:16:04,030 --> 00:16:05,890
Where do you feel uncomfortable?

239
00:16:10,120 --> 00:16:11,320
I'm a police officer.

240
00:16:14,910 --> 00:16:15,580
Well,

241
00:16:16,870 --> 00:16:17,910
there's a case

242
00:16:18,910 --> 00:16:21,080
that's been quite troublesome recently.

243
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:21,790
It's been

244
00:16:22,140 --> 00:16:23,810
keeping me awake all night,

245
00:16:23,870 --> 00:16:26,030
and I can't work properly during the day.

246
00:16:26,030 --> 00:16:28,270
I really don't know what to do,

247
00:16:28,270 --> 00:16:30,360
so I thought I'd come and see

248
00:16:30,550 --> 00:16:32,010
if I could get some relief.

249
00:16:32,910 --> 00:16:34,390
Since you're in this room,

250
00:16:34,390 --> 00:16:35,850
you're just a patient now.

251
00:16:35,870 --> 00:16:37,200
Whatever you say to me,

252
00:16:37,200 --> 00:16:38,850
I am obligated to keep it confidential.

253
00:16:38,850 --> 00:16:40,250
Well then. That's great.

254
00:16:40,630 --> 00:16:43,080
But will what you tell me

255
00:16:43,080 --> 00:16:43,910
include

256
00:16:43,910 --> 00:16:46,240
anything confidential from your system?

257
00:16:46,620 --> 00:16:48,220
That shouldn't be a problem.

258
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:50,910
It's a case from many years ago.

259
00:16:51,630 --> 00:16:53,750
It must have been over a decade ago.

260
00:16:54,860 --> 00:16:55,860
Here's the thing.

261
00:16:58,120 --> 00:17:02,270
An ordinary, virtuous mother

262
00:17:03,670 --> 00:17:05,640
wanted to find a tutor for her son.

263
00:17:06,030 --> 00:17:06,920
Stop talking!

264
00:17:09,069 --> 00:17:10,270
I forgot everything.

265
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:11,480
What if I told you

266
00:17:11,480 --> 00:17:13,880
that your mom left you
and your dad back then

267
00:17:14,300 --> 00:17:15,900
and later committed suicide

268
00:17:17,490 --> 00:17:19,750
because she was deceived by a bad person?

269
00:17:25,270 --> 00:17:26,670
He was a college student.

270
00:17:27,430 --> 00:17:28,430
He was quite nice.

271
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:30,860
Other than tutoring me,

272
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:32,430
he hardly spoke.

273
00:17:33,340 --> 00:17:35,140
Once, when my mom burned her hand

274
00:17:35,440 --> 00:17:36,350
while cooking,

275
00:17:37,110 --> 00:17:39,750
he even used a first-aid kit
to bandage it.

276
00:17:39,960 --> 00:17:41,290
My mom even praised him,

277
00:17:41,790 --> 00:17:44,190
saying that even though
he studied psychiatry,

278
00:17:44,190 --> 00:17:46,920
she didn't expect him
to be so skilled in surgery.

279
00:17:47,160 --> 00:17:48,760
But for some unknown reason,

280
00:17:49,350 --> 00:17:50,360
he got angry.

281
00:17:51,450 --> 00:17:54,580
He didn't come to our house for classes
for several days.

282
00:17:55,190 --> 00:17:56,220
I thought

283
00:17:57,530 --> 00:17:59,190
my mom would get me a new tutor.

284
00:18:00,270 --> 00:18:01,130
To my surprise,

285
00:18:01,830 --> 00:18:02,590
he came back.

286
00:18:04,480 --> 00:18:05,480
Since then,

287
00:18:06,270 --> 00:18:08,480
we became much closer.

288
00:18:10,070 --> 00:18:10,720
Later,

289
00:18:12,200 --> 00:18:14,730
he said he was going to study
in Harbor Island.

290
00:18:15,590 --> 00:18:18,520
My mom even secretly funded him
behind my dad's back.

291
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:23,440
I've thought about it over and over again.

292
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:23,990
If...

293
00:18:26,060 --> 00:18:28,660
If I had noticed something was wrong
back then,

294
00:18:30,200 --> 00:18:31,060
would my mom...

295
00:18:31,270 --> 00:18:32,790
not have left?

296
00:18:33,510 --> 00:18:35,310
It was two years later that the son

297
00:18:35,310 --> 00:18:36,910
heard from his mother again.

298
00:18:37,230 --> 00:18:38,960
He overheard his father's call

299
00:18:40,070 --> 00:18:41,600
and learned that his mother

300
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:43,120
had taken her own life

301
00:18:43,880 --> 00:18:44,800
in Bingyuan.

302
00:18:50,310 --> 00:18:51,070
Don't drink!

303
00:18:54,750 --> 00:18:55,240
Don't.

304
00:18:59,480 --> 00:19:00,880
Do you know how she died?

305
00:19:17,250 --> 00:19:18,850
She was lying in the bathtub,

306
00:19:20,320 --> 00:19:21,320
covered in blood.

307
00:19:22,720 --> 00:19:23,780
She was all frozen,

308
00:19:25,520 --> 00:19:26,930
like an ice sculpture.

309
00:19:30,510 --> 00:19:33,310
The autopsy later revealed
that she was pregnant.

310
00:19:34,750 --> 00:19:35,880
Two lives were lost.

311
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:39,340
And that son...

312
00:19:40,240 --> 00:19:42,790
His mother abandoned him

313
00:19:42,810 --> 00:19:43,940
for so-called love.

314
00:19:44,790 --> 00:19:46,200
His father was always away on business

315
00:19:46,200 --> 00:19:47,440
and had no time for him.

316
00:19:47,440 --> 00:19:49,440
He had to live with his grandmother.

317
00:19:49,510 --> 00:19:50,370
Not long after,

318
00:19:51,030 --> 00:19:53,230
his grandmother died of a broken heart.

319
00:19:53,860 --> 00:19:54,610
Well?

320
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:56,830
A perfectly good family

321
00:19:57,920 --> 00:19:59,380
was ruined just like that.

322
00:20:01,110 --> 00:20:04,070
That bastard who deceived his Mom—

323
00:20:04,720 --> 00:20:06,880
shouldn't he be cut to pieces?

324
00:20:08,630 --> 00:20:09,630
That tutor—

325
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:13,920
what was his name?

326
00:20:17,350 --> 00:20:18,010
Luo Liang.

327
00:20:34,070 --> 00:20:35,470
But from what I've heard,

328
00:20:37,190 --> 00:20:38,900
everything this mother did

329
00:20:39,900 --> 00:20:41,270
was her own choice.

330
00:20:42,830 --> 00:20:44,160
There was no deception.

331
00:20:45,200 --> 00:20:46,730
You sure know a lot about it.

332
00:20:48,400 --> 00:20:49,070
How could I?

333
00:20:49,680 --> 00:20:51,340
As a complete stranger,

334
00:20:51,590 --> 00:20:52,720
how could I know her?

335
00:20:52,720 --> 00:20:54,010
I'm just objectively

336
00:20:54,070 --> 00:20:55,330
analyzing your story.

337
00:20:56,660 --> 00:20:58,320
But what I'm curious about is—

338
00:20:58,940 --> 00:20:59,830
a case from ten years ago

339
00:20:59,830 --> 00:21:01,630
that was already ruled a suicide

340
00:21:02,030 --> 00:21:03,720
and didn't even happen in this city—

341
00:21:03,720 --> 00:21:06,050
why are you reopening the investigation?

342
00:21:10,640 --> 00:21:11,590
I mean,

343
00:21:13,020 --> 00:21:14,050
why is it

344
00:21:14,920 --> 00:21:16,140
bothering you?

345
00:21:19,480 --> 00:21:22,680
This actually involves
confidential case information.

346
00:21:23,160 --> 00:21:24,000
I can't say.

347
00:21:25,480 --> 00:21:26,580
All I can say is,

348
00:21:28,240 --> 00:21:29,070
I think

349
00:21:30,110 --> 00:21:31,910
her suicide was not that simple.

350
00:21:35,110 --> 00:21:36,110
What do you think?

351
00:21:51,640 --> 00:21:53,160
Actually, I don't know anything
about solving cases.

352
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:54,820
I can't answer that question.

353
00:21:55,890 --> 00:21:57,090
Have a piece of candy.

354
00:21:57,640 --> 00:22:00,330
Having something sweet
can help relax your nerves.

355
00:22:00,330 --> 00:22:02,550
You police officers
are under too much stress.

356
00:22:02,550 --> 00:22:03,480
Right, right.

357
00:22:09,780 --> 00:22:11,440
Judging from your condition,

358
00:22:11,880 --> 00:22:13,270
you might have PTSD,

359
00:22:14,350 --> 00:22:16,280
post-traumatic stress disorder.

360
00:22:17,440 --> 00:22:19,240
It could be that the crime scenes

361
00:22:20,070 --> 00:22:21,800
had too much of an impact on you.

362
00:22:23,100 --> 00:22:25,230
It puts psychological pressure on you

363
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:27,030
that you can't process right away.

364
00:22:27,030 --> 00:22:28,760
Actually, this is very normal.

365
00:22:28,790 --> 00:22:30,650
There's nothing to be ashamed of.

366
00:22:30,790 --> 00:22:32,790
And seeking help

367
00:22:32,790 --> 00:22:34,520
from a professional doctor now

368
00:22:34,640 --> 00:22:36,900
is something that should be encouraged.

369
00:22:37,590 --> 00:22:38,790
Thank you. Thank you.

370
00:22:39,680 --> 00:22:40,880
I'll prescribe some medicine for you.

371
00:22:40,880 --> 00:22:41,210
Okay.

372
00:22:42,240 --> 00:22:43,310
I'm glad I'm fine.

373
00:22:46,790 --> 00:22:47,920
Dr. Luo, according to

374
00:22:47,920 --> 00:22:49,270
the profile on the wall outside,

375
00:22:49,270 --> 00:22:51,440
you studied at a university in Chengyu?

376
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:51,920
Yes.

377
00:22:53,130 --> 00:22:54,030
That's a coincidence.

378
00:22:54,030 --> 00:22:56,690
The family I just mentioned
was also in Chengyu.

379
00:22:57,440 --> 00:22:59,430
Wasn't their tutor studying medicine?

380
00:22:59,430 --> 00:23:01,210
Maybe you two met in school.

381
00:23:13,320 --> 00:23:14,520
Li Zhiheng?

382
00:23:14,680 --> 00:23:15,000
Yes.

383
00:23:18,410 --> 00:23:19,550
You are the police officer

384
00:23:19,550 --> 00:23:22,410
who was previously in charge of
Jian Leilei's case?

385
00:23:26,350 --> 00:23:26,830
Yes.

386
00:23:29,590 --> 00:23:30,880
I know Ms. Yan.

387
00:23:33,030 --> 00:23:33,470
Well...

388
00:23:33,470 --> 00:23:35,030
She mentioned to me before

389
00:23:35,030 --> 00:23:37,440
that you are a psychiatrist.

390
00:23:37,440 --> 00:23:39,240
That's why I came here.

391
00:23:39,240 --> 00:23:40,880
It's very hard
to make an appointment with you.

392
00:23:40,880 --> 00:23:42,550
I even paid extra
for a special consultation

393
00:23:42,550 --> 00:23:43,810
just to see you.

394
00:23:44,240 --> 00:23:46,040
You should have told me earlier.

395
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:47,680
In this case,

396
00:23:47,680 --> 00:23:50,280
we have
multiple overlapping relationships.

397
00:23:50,880 --> 00:23:54,280
In principle, it would not be appropriate
for me to treat you.

398
00:23:54,900 --> 00:23:55,440
Is that so?

399
00:23:55,440 --> 00:23:56,750
Well...

400
00:23:56,750 --> 00:23:58,240
I really didn't know that.

401
00:23:58,640 --> 00:23:59,160
I just thought,

402
00:23:59,160 --> 00:24:00,720
since Ms. Yan

403
00:24:00,720 --> 00:24:03,240
is like my own sister,

404
00:24:03,240 --> 00:24:05,340
I should call you brother-in-law.

405
00:24:05,440 --> 00:24:07,880
I'll just say I'm feeling a bit unwell.

406
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:09,090
Coming to see my brother-in-law
for a checkup

407
00:24:09,090 --> 00:24:10,290
is perfectly normal.

408
00:24:11,030 --> 00:24:12,890
So don't worry, brother-in-law.

409
00:24:13,240 --> 00:24:15,170
Ms. Yan's business is my business.

410
00:24:15,590 --> 00:24:16,120
No matter

411
00:24:16,440 --> 00:24:18,200
what happens to my sister,

412
00:24:18,480 --> 00:24:19,640
as her brother,

413
00:24:20,400 --> 00:24:21,600
I will take care of it.

414
00:24:25,270 --> 00:24:27,530
Then I must thank you on her behalf first.

415
00:24:27,960 --> 00:24:28,890
But regardless,

416
00:24:29,440 --> 00:24:31,100
it's best if nothing happens,

417
00:24:31,400 --> 00:24:31,960
right?

418
00:24:32,880 --> 00:24:33,560
Of course.

419
00:24:35,750 --> 00:24:38,550
I've prescribed
some nerve-relaxing pills for you.

420
00:24:38,550 --> 00:24:40,480
Take one when you can't sleep well.

421
00:24:41,090 --> 00:24:42,680
It has a calming effect
and helps you focus.

422
00:24:42,680 --> 00:24:43,510
Okay.

423
00:24:51,830 --> 00:24:54,160
I got this when I was a kid,
playing around,

424
00:24:54,310 --> 00:24:56,440
and burned myself on a kerosene stove.

425
00:24:58,440 --> 00:24:59,840
It looks pretty serious.

426
00:25:00,680 --> 00:25:02,770
Alright, I won't bother you anymore.

427
00:25:04,160 --> 00:25:06,000
Well, we should

428
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:06,640
have a meal together

429
00:25:06,640 --> 00:25:07,920
with Ms. Yan sometime.

430
00:25:08,070 --> 00:25:08,590
No problem.

431
00:25:08,590 --> 00:25:09,750
Let's meet formally.

432
00:25:09,750 --> 00:25:10,080
Okay.

433
00:25:10,720 --> 00:25:10,960
Alright.

434
00:25:10,960 --> 00:25:12,000
I'll let you get back to work.

435
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:12,370
Okay.

436
00:25:13,750 --> 00:25:15,070
You should drink less iced drinks.

437
00:25:15,070 --> 00:25:16,530
It's bad for your stomach.

438
00:25:42,640 --> 00:25:43,700
Hello, Dr. Luo.

439
00:25:43,960 --> 00:25:44,440
Hello.

440
00:27:16,150 --> 00:27:21,590
[Department Dean's Office]

441
00:27:24,880 --> 00:27:26,140
-Mrs. Feng?
-Yan Ling?

442
00:27:27,750 --> 00:27:29,440
You're looking for Director Lin, right?

443
00:27:29,440 --> 00:27:31,440
He's talking with a student inside.

444
00:27:32,960 --> 00:27:34,790
It's fine. I'll wait.

445
00:27:35,650 --> 00:27:36,650
Th-That's fine.

446
00:27:36,680 --> 00:27:37,830
Please wait a moment.

447
00:27:37,830 --> 00:27:40,630
I need to sign a form
at the Student Affairs Office.

448
00:27:41,270 --> 00:27:42,670
I won't keep you company.

449
00:27:42,790 --> 00:27:43,790
Go ahead, please.

450
00:27:49,780 --> 00:27:54,130
[Guo Loulou Street] [Zeze Road]

451
00:28:15,240 --> 00:28:17,410
I want to trim it a bit more.

452
00:28:17,960 --> 00:28:19,180
It'll look nicer if they are crossed.

453
00:28:19,180 --> 00:28:20,160
Crossed?

454
00:28:20,160 --> 00:28:20,650
Not bad.

455
00:28:20,800 --> 00:28:21,900
What about this one?

456
00:28:21,900 --> 00:28:22,500
Stop.

457
00:28:23,240 --> 00:28:24,160
Jiale?

458
00:28:24,550 --> 00:28:25,030
Mom?

459
00:28:25,480 --> 00:28:26,520
Why are you here?

460
00:28:28,350 --> 00:28:29,960
Dr. Luo brought me here.

461
00:28:30,800 --> 00:28:32,730
And we bought flowers for Grandma.

462
00:28:32,740 --> 00:28:35,340
They're the lilies
she and Grandpa liked best.

463
00:28:36,150 --> 00:28:37,880
That's very thoughtful of you.

464
00:28:39,190 --> 00:28:40,590
I didn't even think of it.

465
00:28:41,590 --> 00:28:43,250
We just bought them on the way.

466
00:28:43,510 --> 00:28:46,350
Why are you holding your stomach?
Are you not feeling well?

467
00:28:46,350 --> 00:28:47,750
My stomach is a bit upset.

468
00:28:47,750 --> 00:28:49,430
It's fine.
I'll be okay after resting for a while.

469
00:28:49,430 --> 00:28:50,680
Then go inside and rest.

470
00:28:50,680 --> 00:28:51,140
No need.

471
00:28:51,540 --> 00:28:53,270
Go ahead. I'll take care of him.

472
00:28:56,120 --> 00:28:58,180
Here, Jiale. I'm leaving this to you.

473
00:28:59,940 --> 00:29:00,700
Jiale.

474
00:29:02,030 --> 00:29:03,350
What do you want to eat for dinner?

475
00:29:03,350 --> 00:29:04,880
I will cook it for you, okay?

476
00:29:05,880 --> 00:29:07,210
Anything would be fine.

477
00:29:07,500 --> 00:29:09,500
Cola chicken wings? How about that?

478
00:29:10,480 --> 00:29:10,880
Okay.

479
00:29:11,030 --> 00:29:11,520
Okay.

480
00:29:11,680 --> 00:29:13,280
Let's make it together then.

481
00:29:14,270 --> 00:29:15,130
Go to your room.

482
00:29:15,520 --> 00:29:17,200
-I'll take a nap then.
-Go.

483
00:29:22,040 --> 00:29:22,960
This one hasn't been trimmed yet.

484
00:29:22,960 --> 00:29:23,690
This one has.

485
00:29:25,390 --> 00:29:25,920
Jiale.

486
00:29:27,680 --> 00:29:29,330
A lot of things happened to Mom recently,

487
00:29:29,330 --> 00:29:30,680
and she's not in a good mood.

488
00:29:30,680 --> 00:29:31,550
That's why she forgot

489
00:29:31,550 --> 00:29:33,080
to buy flowers for Grandma.

490
00:29:36,400 --> 00:29:39,380
We were just talking about
Grandpa and Grandma.

491
00:29:39,720 --> 00:29:41,030
Don't ask her about it,

492
00:29:41,630 --> 00:29:43,490
so she won't get sad again.

493
00:29:47,740 --> 00:29:49,430
I miss Grandma a little.

494
00:29:51,830 --> 00:29:55,030
Although she was
very strict with me before,

495
00:29:56,070 --> 00:29:59,200
she was really, really good to me
before she passed away.

496
00:29:59,680 --> 00:30:00,830
If only Mom had apologized

497
00:30:00,830 --> 00:30:02,480
to Grandma earlier.

498
00:30:03,030 --> 00:30:05,490
We could have been
together happily sooner.

499
00:30:11,160 --> 00:30:12,720
Mom is quite stubborn.

500
00:30:13,400 --> 00:30:15,030
We need to be more understanding of her.

501
00:30:15,030 --> 00:30:16,070
We're boys,

502
00:30:17,160 --> 00:30:19,510
so we should be more considerate, okay?

503
00:30:21,070 --> 00:30:23,680
Come on, put the new flowers in quickly.

504
00:30:24,540 --> 00:30:25,600
Then we'll go cook.

505
00:30:25,750 --> 00:30:26,110
Okay?

506
00:30:35,640 --> 00:30:36,480
Chicken wings.

507
00:30:36,480 --> 00:30:37,540
Careful, it's hot.

508
00:30:37,640 --> 00:30:38,110
Jiale,

509
00:30:38,110 --> 00:30:38,640
look.

510
00:30:38,920 --> 00:30:40,030
How's the shrimp I cooked?

511
00:30:40,030 --> 00:30:40,480
Good.

512
00:30:40,630 --> 00:30:41,200
Let's plate it.

513
00:30:41,200 --> 00:30:42,130
Five Blessings.

514
00:30:43,310 --> 00:30:44,710
I'll add some garnish.

515
00:30:44,980 --> 00:30:46,320
Okay, garnish it.

516
00:30:52,920 --> 00:30:53,500
Jiale.

517
00:30:53,920 --> 00:30:55,160
This is called parsley.

518
00:30:55,160 --> 00:30:57,090
Help me sprinkle some later, okay?

519
00:30:59,160 --> 00:30:59,550
Here.

520
00:31:01,590 --> 00:31:02,760
Chef.

521
00:31:10,880 --> 00:31:11,920
I'm sorry.

522
00:31:12,400 --> 00:31:14,000
I just wanted to take a short nap.

523
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:15,600
I didn't expect to sleep so long.

524
00:31:15,600 --> 00:31:17,240
It's fine. You're up just in time.

525
00:31:17,240 --> 00:31:18,200
I was afraid you'd sleep too long

526
00:31:18,200 --> 00:31:19,730
and the food would get cold.

527
00:31:20,070 --> 00:31:21,930
Is there anything I can help with?

528
00:31:22,000 --> 00:31:22,640
It's fine.

529
00:31:22,880 --> 00:31:24,160
Your cooking is just so-so anyway.

530
00:31:24,160 --> 00:31:25,790
Look at what Dr. Luo and I made.

531
00:31:25,790 --> 00:31:27,720
It can rival Godmother's cooking.

532
00:31:32,400 --> 00:31:34,380
Looks like I really need to learn.

533
00:31:34,550 --> 00:31:36,400
No need, just stay there

534
00:31:36,400 --> 00:31:37,680
and let us serve you.

535
00:31:37,790 --> 00:31:38,310
Yeah.

536
00:31:38,590 --> 00:31:40,550
Before, it was Godmother and Grandma
serving you.

537
00:31:40,550 --> 00:31:41,720
Now it's our turn.

538
00:31:48,680 --> 00:31:49,510
Yan Jiale,

539
00:31:50,000 --> 00:31:52,130
you're being ungrateful saying that.

540
00:31:52,680 --> 00:31:54,830
Who usually folds your clothes

541
00:31:54,880 --> 00:31:56,140
and washes your shoes?

542
00:31:56,200 --> 00:31:57,730
Grandma used to do them too.

543
00:32:02,270 --> 00:32:03,110
Jiale,

544
00:32:03,440 --> 00:32:04,720
be considerate.

545
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:06,550
Cola is probably hungry too.

546
00:32:06,550 --> 00:32:07,410
Help me feed it.

547
00:32:07,790 --> 00:32:08,240
Okay.

548
00:32:09,070 --> 00:32:09,400
Wait,

549
00:32:09,400 --> 00:32:09,960
Mom.

550
00:32:13,400 --> 00:32:15,400
Wipe off any unboiled water from it.

551
00:32:15,510 --> 00:32:18,370
Cola will get diarrhea
if it drinks unboiled water.

552
00:32:19,960 --> 00:32:20,790
Got it.

553
00:32:22,070 --> 00:32:24,200
You don't even care about me that much.

554
00:32:24,310 --> 00:32:25,510
You're not a hamster.

555
00:32:26,550 --> 00:32:27,810
Jiale, serve the food.

556
00:32:28,430 --> 00:32:29,550
What are we missing?

557
00:32:29,550 --> 00:32:30,750
Let's make some okra.

558
00:32:30,770 --> 00:32:31,240
Okay.

559
00:32:31,960 --> 00:32:32,960
You add the sauce.

560
00:32:33,750 --> 00:32:34,680
Just like a chef,

561
00:32:34,680 --> 00:32:36,140
sprinkle it on with flair.

562
00:32:42,180 --> 00:32:43,340
Like a lion.

563
00:32:43,590 --> 00:32:44,070
Lion.

564
00:32:44,510 --> 00:32:45,840
Show your canine teeth.

565
00:32:48,480 --> 00:32:49,880
The left side.

566
00:32:50,920 --> 00:32:51,440
Left.

567
00:32:51,960 --> 00:32:53,070
Right side.

568
00:32:54,790 --> 00:32:56,000
Okay, all clean.

569
00:32:56,110 --> 00:32:56,720
Spit.

570
00:32:58,750 --> 00:33:00,210
Come on, let's go to sleep.

571
00:33:01,550 --> 00:33:02,670
Good night, Mom.

572
00:33:02,790 --> 00:33:03,450
Good night.

573
00:33:04,270 --> 00:33:04,960
Fly!

574
00:33:07,680 --> 00:33:09,610
Come, get under the covers, Jiale.

575
00:33:12,270 --> 00:33:12,930
Go to sleep.

576
00:33:24,250 --> 00:33:26,280
You should have told me in advance.

577
00:33:26,920 --> 00:33:27,960
Jiale is back,

578
00:33:28,120 --> 00:33:29,850
but I didn't even get prepared.

579
00:33:34,160 --> 00:33:35,220
Are you blaming me?

580
00:33:36,480 --> 00:33:37,000
No.

581
00:33:38,400 --> 00:33:40,160
I wanted to give you a surprise.

582
00:33:41,200 --> 00:33:42,600
I thought you'd be happy.

583
00:33:43,310 --> 00:33:44,710
I'm Jiale's stepfather.

584
00:33:45,350 --> 00:33:46,480
And he likes me.

585
00:33:47,310 --> 00:33:49,590
I thought you'd be happy to see all this,

586
00:33:50,550 --> 00:33:51,200
but I didn't expect that

587
00:33:51,200 --> 00:33:52,720
your concern would be

588
00:33:53,070 --> 00:33:55,530
that I brought him back
without telling you.

589
00:33:56,480 --> 00:33:57,310
Of course I'm happy

590
00:33:57,310 --> 00:33:58,790
that you brought him back.

591
00:34:01,200 --> 00:34:02,550
Why are you angry?

592
00:34:03,750 --> 00:34:04,400
No.

593
00:34:05,590 --> 00:34:07,920
Your tone just now was very strange.

594
00:34:09,110 --> 00:34:10,310
Even if it weren't me,

595
00:34:10,550 --> 00:34:12,070
just an ordinary friend—

596
00:34:12,480 --> 00:34:14,610
like the mother of Jiale's classmate—

597
00:34:14,880 --> 00:34:16,400
if she brought Jiale home,

598
00:34:16,550 --> 00:34:18,670
would you question her first,

599
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:20,360
asking why she did it,

600
00:34:20,760 --> 00:34:22,400
instead of thanking her?

601
00:34:22,670 --> 00:34:24,550
How could I be questioning you?

602
00:34:25,190 --> 00:34:27,710
I'm very grateful
that you brought Jiale back

603
00:34:27,710 --> 00:34:29,370
and bought flowers for my mom.

604
00:34:30,110 --> 00:34:31,110
What I mean is,

605
00:34:31,110 --> 00:34:32,880
in the future,
if you make arrangements like this,

606
00:34:32,880 --> 00:34:34,800
could you let me know in advance

607
00:34:35,070 --> 00:34:36,400
so I can be prepared?

608
00:34:38,190 --> 00:34:38,670
Okay.

609
00:34:39,550 --> 00:34:40,230
I got it.

610
00:34:40,960 --> 00:34:41,820
It's my fault.

611
00:34:42,190 --> 00:34:44,000
From now on, every message Jiale sends me,

612
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:44,960
every call he makes,

613
00:34:44,960 --> 00:34:46,690
I'll report to you completely.

614
00:34:46,760 --> 00:34:48,190
If he ever asks me to pick him up,

615
00:34:48,190 --> 00:34:49,590
I'll make sure I have

616
00:34:49,590 --> 00:34:50,280
your permission first.

617
00:34:50,280 --> 00:34:51,070
Is that okay?

618
00:34:51,360 --> 00:34:52,880
I didn't mean that.

619
00:34:53,920 --> 00:34:55,850
Why are you being so unreasonable?

620
00:34:56,659 --> 00:34:58,440
Me? I'm being unreasonable?

621
00:34:58,590 --> 00:35:00,280
Now it's me who's being unreasonable?

622
00:35:00,280 --> 00:35:01,900
I know you've been in a bad mood lately,

623
00:35:01,900 --> 00:35:03,510
and you're not feeling well today.

624
00:35:03,510 --> 00:35:05,760
I picked Jiale up, cooked, and cleaned up,

625
00:35:05,760 --> 00:35:07,360
and I'm being unreasonable?

626
00:35:09,330 --> 00:35:10,400
Jiale and I guessed that

627
00:35:10,400 --> 00:35:12,510
you'd be super happy
to see him when you got back.

628
00:35:12,510 --> 00:35:14,000
You weren't as happy as we imagined,

629
00:35:14,000 --> 00:35:14,800
which is fine,

630
00:35:14,970 --> 00:35:16,080
but you had absolutely no reaction

631
00:35:16,080 --> 00:35:17,240
to our efforts.

632
00:35:17,550 --> 00:35:19,330
It's okay if you wrong me,

633
00:35:19,400 --> 00:35:20,940
but it's not fair to Jiale.

634
00:35:21,320 --> 00:35:22,920
How could I have no reaction?

635
00:35:24,320 --> 00:35:25,920
I know you've done a lot.

636
00:35:26,070 --> 00:35:27,190
-I'm so gr-
-Forget it.

637
00:35:27,190 --> 00:35:28,110
Let's leave it at that.

638
00:35:28,110 --> 00:35:30,960
We've been arguing for so long
over such a small thing.

639
00:35:30,960 --> 00:35:31,590
I'll go wash up outside.

640
00:35:31,590 --> 00:35:33,160
I didn't blame you.

641
00:35:33,190 --> 00:35:33,550
I...

642
00:35:47,150 --> 00:35:47,960
Honey.

643
00:35:50,000 --> 00:35:51,580
Honey, don't be angry.

644
00:35:51,760 --> 00:35:53,080
Listen to me.

645
00:35:53,280 --> 00:35:54,760
I didn't blame you.

646
00:35:55,070 --> 00:35:56,440
You misunderstood me.

647
00:36:22,920 --> 00:36:23,980
Have some hot milk.

648
00:36:24,280 --> 00:36:25,740
It helps you sleep better.

649
00:36:32,110 --> 00:36:35,000
Honey, I really didn't blame you just now,

650
00:36:35,800 --> 00:36:37,730
but you suddenly lost your temper.

651
00:36:38,480 --> 00:36:40,610
I don't even know how to talk to you now.

652
00:36:42,800 --> 00:36:44,360
Alright, alright.

653
00:36:44,510 --> 00:36:45,230
I know.

654
00:36:46,400 --> 00:36:47,590
My bad, okay?

655
00:36:49,890 --> 00:36:51,170
I'm not mad at you.

656
00:36:52,110 --> 00:36:53,240
You're in a bad mood.

657
00:36:53,480 --> 00:36:54,510
Did you go to the school again

658
00:36:54,510 --> 00:36:55,770
and something happen?

659
00:36:59,880 --> 00:37:02,070
I waited outside Director Lin's office

660
00:37:02,070 --> 00:37:03,110
for a long time,

661
00:37:04,070 --> 00:37:05,730
but in the end, I didn't get in.

662
00:37:09,590 --> 00:37:10,230
Why?

663
00:37:11,880 --> 00:37:13,760
I saw Mrs. Feng at the door.

664
00:37:15,110 --> 00:37:17,040
I feel like she's been avoiding me.

665
00:37:18,710 --> 00:37:20,280
And the way she looked at me

666
00:37:20,920 --> 00:37:23,760
was as if she believed
I was that kind of person.

667
00:37:25,480 --> 00:37:26,680
I didn't want to go in.

668
00:37:27,280 --> 00:37:29,080
I didn't know what to say to them.

669
00:37:33,280 --> 00:37:36,080
You don't need to beg
for their forgiveness at all.

670
00:37:37,190 --> 00:37:39,190
Since they make you uncomfortable,

671
00:37:39,330 --> 00:37:40,400
we shouldn't give them

672
00:37:40,400 --> 00:37:42,200
the right to give you a hard time.

673
00:37:42,530 --> 00:37:44,590
We'll mind our own business from now on.

674
00:37:44,590 --> 00:37:45,800
Why do you have to

675
00:37:45,800 --> 00:37:46,480
beg them so pathetically,

676
00:37:46,480 --> 00:37:47,510
letting them pity

677
00:37:48,150 --> 00:37:49,080
and laugh at you?

678
00:37:52,760 --> 00:37:54,090
After I left the school,

679
00:37:55,400 --> 00:37:57,400
I sat alone in the car for a long time.

680
00:37:58,400 --> 00:38:00,530
I can say with a clear conscience that,

681
00:38:00,710 --> 00:38:01,670
as a teacher,

682
00:38:02,670 --> 00:38:04,670
my academic level is up to standard,

683
00:38:05,760 --> 00:38:07,590
and I am conscientious and responsible

684
00:38:07,590 --> 00:38:08,720
toward my students.

685
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:12,150
Although morally,

686
00:38:13,230 --> 00:38:14,160
I have a blemish,

687
00:38:16,000 --> 00:38:17,280
isn't Ding Zhibo

688
00:38:17,280 --> 00:38:18,590
the real culprit?

689
00:38:20,070 --> 00:38:21,530
If I just resign like this,

690
00:38:22,320 --> 00:38:24,590
won't it show
that I have a guilty conscience

691
00:38:24,590 --> 00:38:26,390
and confirm their opinion of me?

692
00:38:28,320 --> 00:38:28,920
Honey,

693
00:38:30,510 --> 00:38:31,510
I don't want this.

694
00:38:32,510 --> 00:38:34,440
I don't want to back down like this.

695
00:38:40,000 --> 00:38:40,590
Okay.

696
00:38:41,670 --> 00:38:44,000
I'll support whatever decision you make.

697
00:38:44,320 --> 00:38:46,000
Don't think about anything now.

698
00:38:46,000 --> 00:38:47,000
Go to sleep first.

699
00:38:47,320 --> 00:38:48,590
We'll talk tomorrow.

700
00:38:52,960 --> 00:38:53,590
Honey,

701
00:38:54,400 --> 00:38:55,670
don't be angry.

702
00:38:56,920 --> 00:38:59,520
I know everything
you've done for me and Jiale.

703
00:39:00,550 --> 00:39:01,960
I'm very grateful to you.

704
00:39:04,960 --> 00:39:05,760
It's fine.

705
00:39:06,590 --> 00:39:07,590
I'm not angry.

706
00:39:08,880 --> 00:39:09,360
Really.

707
00:39:11,360 --> 00:39:12,190
I'm not angry.

708
00:39:36,360 --> 00:39:37,070
Yuan.

709
00:39:37,630 --> 00:39:39,560
Mom will make you a bowl of wontons.

710
00:39:42,040 --> 00:39:42,920
What's wrong?

711
00:39:43,320 --> 00:39:43,920
Yuan?

712
00:39:45,150 --> 00:39:45,950
What's wrong?

713
00:39:51,510 --> 00:39:52,510
Yuan!

714
00:39:53,230 --> 00:39:54,150
Yuan!

715
00:39:56,830 --> 00:40:00,400
[Son]

716
00:40:02,930 --> 00:40:07,250
[Son]

717
00:40:07,310 --> 00:40:09,700
[Wuzhou People's Hospital]

718
00:40:12,680 --> 00:40:14,110
[Emergency Room]

719
00:40:18,610 --> 00:40:20,460
[Emergency Room]

720
00:40:19,920 --> 00:40:21,840
Who are Xiao Yuan's family members?

721
00:40:21,840 --> 00:40:31,170
[Chinese Pharmacy] [Western Pharmacy]
[Emergency Ultrasound Room] [Injection Room]

722
00:40:21,930 --> 00:40:22,440
I am.

723
00:40:22,550 --> 00:40:23,170
I am.

724
00:40:23,760 --> 00:40:25,400
How is my daughter?

725
00:40:26,710 --> 00:40:28,620
She's temporarily out of danger.

726
00:40:29,070 --> 00:40:30,110
If you had come 10 minutes later,

727
00:40:30,110 --> 00:40:32,240
we might not have been able to save her.

728
00:40:33,760 --> 00:40:34,230
Well...

729
00:40:35,150 --> 00:40:36,880
what exactly is wrong with her?

730
00:40:37,670 --> 00:40:39,440
You don't know?

731
00:40:39,550 --> 00:40:40,880
She has drug poisoning.

732
00:40:40,960 --> 00:40:41,440
Drug?

733
00:40:41,920 --> 00:40:42,630
Poisoning?

734
00:40:45,110 --> 00:40:47,170
What medicine does she usually take?

735
00:40:49,840 --> 00:40:55,250
[Emergency Room]

736
00:40:50,110 --> 00:40:52,110
She has a mental illness.

737
00:40:52,800 --> 00:40:54,930
The medicine she takes is all for this.

738
00:40:55,760 --> 00:40:56,840
I can't read.

739
00:40:57,400 --> 00:40:59,800
I can only give her the pills
by their color.

740
00:41:00,070 --> 00:41:02,800
Then which hospital did you take her to?

741
00:41:02,880 --> 00:41:05,480
Which doctor prescribed
the medicine for her?

742
00:41:06,550 --> 00:41:08,800
A doctor from out of town.

743
00:41:09,150 --> 00:41:09,960
A...

744
00:41:10,110 --> 00:41:11,960
A doctor from our hometown.

745
00:41:13,960 --> 00:41:16,480
What about the burns on her body?

746
00:41:17,360 --> 00:41:17,880
Well...

747
00:41:18,550 --> 00:41:19,840
I don't know.

748
00:41:20,360 --> 00:41:21,510
She went out to work

749
00:41:21,880 --> 00:41:23,550
and came back like this.

750
00:41:24,320 --> 00:41:26,030
And her mind was also damaged.

751
00:41:27,190 --> 00:41:27,840
I see.

752
00:41:28,400 --> 00:41:29,800
Wait here first.

753
00:41:29,800 --> 00:41:30,800
I'll go get you a form.

754
00:41:30,800 --> 00:41:32,460
She needs to be hospitalized.

755
00:41:32,550 --> 00:41:33,840
Don't move. Just wait.

756
00:41:34,800 --> 00:41:35,280
Okay.

757
00:41:41,190 --> 00:41:42,070
Call the police immediately.

758
00:41:42,070 --> 00:41:44,470
There's something wrong with this mother.

759
00:41:48,470 --> 00:41:54,930
[July 12, 2019, Friday]
[Case Filing Chamber]

760
00:41:48,880 --> 00:41:50,030
Think harder.

761
00:41:50,590 --> 00:41:52,520
See if there are any other details.

762
00:42:04,070 --> 00:42:05,130
I'll ask you again.

763
00:42:05,800 --> 00:42:06,840
What's

764
00:42:07,510 --> 00:42:09,400
your relationship with this girl?

765
00:42:09,400 --> 00:42:10,540
She's my daughter.

766
00:42:11,670 --> 00:42:12,280
Ma'am,

767
00:42:13,070 --> 00:42:14,190
you have type O blood,

768
00:42:14,190 --> 00:42:15,590
and she has type AB blood.

769
00:42:15,920 --> 00:42:17,450
Do you know what that means?

770
00:42:18,340 --> 00:42:19,080
No.

771
00:42:19,760 --> 00:42:20,670
It means

772
00:42:21,000 --> 00:42:23,000
she couldn't possibly be your daughter.

773
00:42:23,000 --> 00:42:24,070
Who exactly is she?

774
00:42:25,070 --> 00:42:25,470
She...

775
00:42:25,960 --> 00:42:27,440
is my daughter.

776
00:42:31,880 --> 00:42:33,400
Then where did these pills you gave her

777
00:42:33,400 --> 00:42:34,440
come from?

778
00:42:34,920 --> 00:42:36,850
These are all prescription drugs.

779
00:42:36,880 --> 00:42:38,480
Without a doctor's prescription,

780
00:42:38,480 --> 00:42:40,740
you can't buy them at a regular pharmacy.

781
00:42:41,440 --> 00:42:43,570
Which doctor prescribed them for her?

782
00:42:44,270 --> 00:42:48,970
[The Dark Romance]

783
00:42:51,440 --> 00:42:52,580
I've turned it off!

784
00:42:52,750 --> 00:42:53,800
The fire is gone now.

785
00:42:53,800 --> 00:42:54,480
Fire, fire!

786
00:42:54,710 --> 00:42:55,880
The fire is gone now! It's gone!

787
00:42:55,880 --> 00:42:57,280
Stand up!

788
00:42:57,590 --> 00:42:58,220
Mom!

789
00:42:58,480 --> 00:42:59,140
Mom's here.

790
00:42:59,650 --> 00:43:00,310
Mom's here.

791
00:43:00,390 --> 00:43:01,300
After I leave,

792
00:43:02,590 --> 00:43:04,420
remember to give her the medicine.

793
00:43:04,420 --> 00:43:06,550
I've already put it in the nightstand.

794
00:43:06,840 --> 00:43:08,170
Don't miss a single day.

795
00:43:08,840 --> 00:43:12,070
The small ones,
2 times a day, 3 pills each time.

796
00:43:12,590 --> 00:43:15,000
The big ones, 3 times a day,

797
00:43:15,000 --> 00:43:15,890
4 pills each time.

798
00:43:15,890 --> 00:43:17,450
What illness does she have

799
00:43:18,070 --> 00:43:19,800
that she needs to take so much medicine?

800
00:43:19,800 --> 00:43:20,800
You don't need to ask.

801
00:43:20,800 --> 00:43:22,330
Just give her the medicine.

802
00:43:24,050 --> 00:43:26,490
I have a bad memory and can't remember it.

803
00:43:26,550 --> 00:43:27,800
I'll write it down.

804
00:43:27,800 --> 00:43:29,030
Don't write it down.

805
00:43:29,030 --> 00:43:31,330
Just keep it in your mind.

806
00:43:31,550 --> 00:43:33,670
Not a day missed, and not a pill less.

807
00:43:35,520 --> 00:43:36,730
Take good care of her.

808
00:43:37,620 --> 00:43:38,910
I'll pack up and go back.
